text: I call my mother at least once a week. However last week I completely forgot. This morning she called me, she thought I felt ill.

label: guilt
text: One night during dinner my nephew was naughty, so I quarrelled with my  parents.   I regreted this as my nephew was only two years old and I  had to tolerate him !  The quarrel made my father think that his children  may not take care of him in the future (it was a slip of the tongue and  this made me realize that my father keeps his thoughts to himself).  I was  still very angry so I dropped my bowl and chopsticks and went to the kitchen  to drink tea and then ran to the other side of the house.

label: guilt
text: When the student union leaders were expelled from the university and we continued to study.

label: guilt
text: [ No response.]

label: guilt
text: I had wasted some time instead of doing something I needed to do to give to a friend. (Also in the time I wasted I had done some things I did not consider morally right).

label: guilt
text: Made a mistake at work.

label: guilt
text: Some boys talking about nicknames of the lecturers, and I was too afraid of them to stop them.

label: guilt
text: I had a quarrel with near persons. I said many ill-considered things and I regretted it when it was to late.

label: guilt
text: Being rude to someone I do not like.

label: guilt
text: I stole a coconut cake from a reception table and when I put in my mouth I realized that the host was watching me.

label: guilt
text: When I was caught going out with another girl by my girlfriend.

label: guilt
text: I felt guilty after getting really angry with a friend and having an argument. I was being stubborn and proud, and selfish, because my friend let me down, through no fault of her own.

label: guilt
text: Once I worked as a designer. A fitter was hard hit in a damage that occurred at the building site I had designed.

label: guilt
text: My younger sister wanted to take classes to learn a musical instrument.  One Saturday morning my mother asked me to go with        her for the registration.  I did not want to go  so I said that there might be many bad people at the club.  As a resullt my sister was scolded by my mother.

label: guilt
text: The first time I went away with my boyfriend and lied about where we were staying.

label: guilt
text: When I didn't pass the examinations for FUVEST I felt myself guilty for I should have studied. I had the opportunities, and I drew them out.

label: guilt
text: When my pet dog,who was to us a family member, died.  He had been vomitting for the past three days and we had not found the time to call a vet, finally when the vet came it was already too late.

label: guilt
text: I felt guilt when my friends were punished to slash grass at the gound because of making noise in class. I was in the group of noise-makers but I denied having done any noise.

label: guilt
text: When I scored the third goal to my own side at a football match against William Murray Secondary School and we were badly defeated.

label: guilt
text: I stole carrots and got caught.  I had to apologize to the owner.

label: guilt
text: When I betrayed my lover, she told me something in confidence, I felt at the time I had to relay the information back to the person concerned, as I felt the situation volitile, did this without telling my lover, she felt like piggy in the middle, as she was not directly concerned. Maybe you could call it gossip I felt different after I had slept on it. If I had waited, thought, NOW I would not have done it.

label: guilt
text: I once stole my father's money and denied having done it. Instead father threatened my young brother and he was beaten. He was innocent and I felt guilty.

label: guilt
text: When I offend somebody unfairly.

label: guilt
text: [ No response.]

label: guilt
text: I got up late and I could not go to my lessons on time.  When I entered the class room the stare of the teacher and my classmates made me feel guilty.

label: guilt
text: I had stopped talking to a very close friend of mine.  A week later he came over to try and make friends with me  again and from the way he talked I felt that he was a very mean preson.

label: guilt
text: I had promised to do a task for someone that was close to me, and from the outset I knew it was important that I do it, but when it came to it, I let them down.

label: guilt
text: I feel always guilty before my parents when I come home and have to tell them I have failed an exam.

label: guilt
text: Getting a D in a class last semester and knowing it was because I didn't study.

label: guilt
text: We had promised, with a friend of mine, to take our friends to a restaurant and after having looked for a place for hours without finding one, and not being helped by the others we had to give up the idea.

label: guilt
text: When ,due to hunger and tiredness, I became generally irritated with my fiancee and made cutting remarks which really hurt him.  Later I realized that my unfounded irritation had hurt the person I love most on earth.

label: guilt
text: I removed an article of clothing belonging to my employer while in a position of trust.

label: guilt
text: When some housemen told me a young girl like you should not be allowed to lecture to consultants, I was too shy to argue against them.

label: guilt
text: I felt guilty when I heard the results of my friend, who had failed.  I wished that I had helped him.

label: guilt
text: Years ago I ran away from home which disappointed my parents.

label: guilt
text: I was on a visit to friends who have a baby. The baby was crying in another room, but soon it became quieter and it seemed that it would fall asleep. I went into the room where the baby was lying - and it started crying again.

label: guilt
text: Once I lied to my parents and this made me feel very guilty.

label: guilt
text: When my boyfriend asked me to go out with him and I refused because I wanted to go out with another guy.  I did go out and my boyfriend found out.

label: guilt
text: When my mother returned from a holiday, I told her a lie i.e my father had brought another woman home while she was away.

label: guilt
text: The day I came home drunk after having attended a disco party.

label: guilt
text: When I was forced to decline the invitation to my mother's 70th birthday because of my work committments in another area.

label: guilt
text: Slept with someone close to my girlfriend and myself.

label: guilt
text: Always, and this happens often when I do not keep my word.

label: guilt
text: [ No response.]

label: guilt
text: I know that a certain person feels very lonely, and that she always looks forward to seeing me. However, often I am too busy to visit her, then I feel guilty.

label: guilt
text: I had thrown with the ashtray a still lighted cigarette in the plastic wastepaper basket. It had burnt out and my landlords made me a row that I might had set their flat on fire.

label: guilt
text: I did badly in one of the vital exams, despite getting proper guidance from my parents.  I felt guilty of improper use of the chances provided to me.

label: guilt
text: I let my pet budgie loose to fly around my room one afternoon. A few hours afterwards I found he was still free, went in and out of my room leaving the door open. My cat got in and killed my budgie - this happened to 3 budgies.

label: guilt
text: [ No response.]

label: guilt
text: I felt guilty last year during the winter term exams. A colleague of mine asked me to give him my lecture notes (I had very good notes and I had passed my exam in advance) but I still don't know why I didn't give them to him. That colleague failed and he was on the verge of not passing it at the supplementary examinations.

label: guilt
text: I borrowed my classmate's notebook one week before the examination and I promised to give it back to her in two days time.  I was very busy at that time and forgot many things; as I was not very often at home she could not contact me.  When I started my revision I realized that her notebook had been on my desk for five days.  I contacted her immediately and gave it back to her.  Though she did not say anything I felt very guilty.

label: guilt
text: [ Generally when I am shopping I feel like I were guilty of all the thefts through the year (I have never stolen).]

label: guilt
text: When I cheated my father about the book allowance at university.  He discovered that we were given K150 per year for books.

label: guilt
text: When I had had the possibility to act or to do certain activity better but I had not done it because of reluctance or carelessness.

label: guilt
text: One day my mother went to visit her friends.  When she came back she scolded me for not having kept the house in order, so I decided not to talk to her.

label: guilt
text: When one has neglected or been unjust to a good friend.

label: guilt
text: [ If one has planned to do something \important\" and then, for √°|some reason, fails to do it.]"

label: guilt
text: When I laughed at a lame man walking down the road, it looked funny at the time but later I felt lousy.  It was the same day that I had stolen some coins from my mother in the shop.

label: guilt
text: A lonely, neurotic, shy girl lives nearby. She has expressed a wish to meet me, I have however avoided her (turned down an invitation) as the crisis my partner is going through uses up all my empathy.

label: guilt
text: [ No answer as I see very little difference between shame and guilt.  Therefore see answer for \shame\".]"

label: guilt
text: I felt guilty when I lied to my parents.

label: guilt
text: When I inadvertantly made some close friends and relatives feel bad.

label: guilt
text: When I could not complete my assignment on time.

label: guilt
text: My mother wants to talk very often about her life. I dislike this because she always talks negatively about the same people whatever I do it doesn't help.

label: guilt
text: When I realized that I was not working hard enough and was not being useful as an individual to the society or the family, guilt at spending money on uncalled for activities - in short wasting my life.

label: guilt
text: When I shouted and quarrelled and for no reason I had been rude to my mother and when my behaviour had been influenced by other outward factors.

label: guilt
text: Squeezed the puppy in the door.

label: guilt
text: I was on a concert-tour and therefor seperated from my boy-friend. But I needed warmth which was given by a male member of the orchestra. My feelings towards him were not very deep, but his feelings were. I felt guilty when he said \I am not a √°|radiator\".

label: guilt
text: I felt guilty when I lied to my parents.

label: guilt
text: I felt guilty of revealing a secret to my in-law. I told her that my brother and I had gone to disconight which is a thing my brother didn't want to let her know. Later my brother was accused of spending a night out.

label: guilt
text: It was on January 1st 1985 when I accidentally broke a Fanta bottle in a certain bottle store in Zomba.

label: guilt
text: When I cheated my trusting girlfriend by telling her that I was a qualified doctor and later she found out that I was only a medical student at the preclinical level.

label: guilt
text: Our Headmaster came to our hostel. The lights were off but there was a lot of noise. We shouted at him when he knocked at our door. We later saw that it was the Headmaster.

label: guilt
text: I did not attend a social studies observation class for 1 whole week (I am a student trainee teacher). Anyway the other teachers thought this was okay because the teacher I was supposed to observe was not well liked. The teacher was in fact really nice to me - but I wanted to get out of teaching a hard topic he had given me.

label: guilt
text: Could not buy a reference book because I got up too late to cue.

label: guilt
text: When a classmate wanted to sit down, I pulled his chair away, so that he was slightly injured.

label: guilt
text: I forgot to convey an important announcement.

label: guilt
text: When before the last exam I have taken, I went out instead of studying.

label: guilt
text: I had promised to send something to a friend and it completely slipped my mind.  I felt guilty for having forgotten.

label: guilt
text: When I see that my mother forces my little brother (15 years) to work very hard for school. I don't agree that she constantly puts him to work, but I don't tell it to her, so nothing changes.

label: guilt
text: I was walking quite quickly and unthinking through a children's playground, when a toddler ran in front of me I knocked him over and he hit his head quite hard and began crying.

label: guilt
text: When my little brother asked me to play with him, I told him that I had no time and that I would play with him the next day. However, the next day I said the same thing.

label: guilt
text: After I had cheated my parents that I had lost my textbooks so they had to send me money.

label: guilt
text: A friend of mine shot himself through the head after having told me and others that he would do so.

label: guilt
text: I had undertaken to help my sister for her class work but some unexpected circumstances prevented me from doing that.

label: guilt
text: A situation where I stole a friends wife's wallet.

label: guilt
text: At a moment of affect I offended a person very close to me. He had given me ground for that but it was a trifling in comparison with the way I insulted him. A moment later I felt a sense of guilt.

label: guilt
text: After yelling at my girlfriend, I felt bad because she was ? crying and upset.

label: guilt
text: I felt guilty the other day because I took two pieces of bread instead of one in the Cafeteria and some of the girls were short of bread.

label: guilt
text: [ No response.]

label: guilt
text: I made another person cry for an unjustified cause.

label: guilt
text: There were old people in a crowded bus and I did not have the courage to give them my seat.  I closed my eyes to sleep and then opened my book to read.  In my heart I wanted to give them the seat.

label: guilt
text: I was to take a test and I had not made the necessary preparations until it was too late.  There were two days to go and I still had not done much.

label: guilt
text: I did not reply to my friend's letter in time.

label: guilt
text: I was alone at home when I broke a figure and then mended it.  A few days later my mother noticed it and asked me about it, I told her that I had no idea.

label: guilt
text: My friend did not do well in the examn because I did not help him.

label: guilt
text: I often feel guilty, and it has to do with other people, e.g. if I haven't visited my older relatives for a while.

label: guilt
text: [ No response.]

label: guilt
text: I work at a commercial house from 7 to 10 a.m. On a very cold day in winter I was late - and let a fellow worker stand in the cold for half an hour.

label: guilt
text: My mother wrote me and said that I would not writ enough letters home.

label: guilt
text: When I was face to face with my deceived friend after sleeping with his wife.

label: guilt
text: When I beat up my son for having beaten up his sister.

label: guilt
text: [ No response.]

label: guilt
text: One day my mother forced me to eat more and I refused, the next day she served me more rice and mutton pieces than usual.  When I saw this I got very angry and scolded her, and refused to eat.  Later I felt guilty and asked her to excuse me.

label: guilt
text: I couldn't fulfill a promise.

label: guilt
text: I felt guilt to have come back from home without seeing my father. When I went home he was at work.

label: guilt
text: I was supposed to fetch some friends at the bus stop, but I did not do it because my father was in a bad mood and I was afraid that he would grumble.

label: guilt
text: I had been together with my boy-friend for two and a half years, when he got to know another girl and not even tried to conceal that from me. I drew my conclusions and left him - I also felt a bit guilty for what had happened.

label: guilt
text: The death of my father made me feel quite guilty, because my attitude towards him had been cold and indifferent.

label: guilt
text: When my boyfriend was away, I flirted with his best friend; I felt guilty the next day.

label: guilt
text: [ No response.]

label: guilt
text: Not beeing able to stay with my mother for the National Day holiday.

label: guilt
text: I saved up money for a good purpose. As I also have to organise a party I am afraid there will rest only a little money for the good purpose I feel guilty about this.

label: guilt
text: When my father (physically handicapped) asks me to do something and I raise several objections. Often I can fix it in few moments.

label: guilt
text: I had an argument with a friend of mine.  She would not let me speak and then I began to shout at her.  She got angry and left, I did not try to prevent her from leaving.

label: guilt
text: When I demand too much from my friends.

label: guilt
text: A borrowed car broke down while I was using it.  It was not my fault, nevertheless I felt guilty.

label: guilt
text: I did not deliver a message on time.

label: guilt
text: When I could not fulfill my expectations.

label: guilt
text: Not attending school, when  am not sick - but in need of mental rest. Staff on your return query your \sickness\" - it is easier √°|in N.Z. to be sick, rather than confide other personal reasons √°|etc."

label: guilt
text: My cousin knocked on the door, looking for me to get her watch back.  I had given it to my girlfriend, Lizzy, as a present.

label: guilt
text: When I think that I have been too stict or narrow minded towards my students.

label: guilt
text: I felt guilty when the truth was known about my impregnating the girl we were staying with.

label: guilt
text: Sleeping through crew practice one Monday morning.

label: guilt
text: When I was reproved eighth grade of high school.

label: guilt
text: This situation happened when my friend me with a knife which I stole from him.

label: guilt
text: About the girl (22 years, married) I felt guilty of the relationship.

label: guilt
text: During an argument with my brother, I behaved rather intransigently, even cruelly, wishing to morally hurt the \person\" √°|opposed to me."

label: guilt
text: One day, I was alone on duty when a patient choked while eating.  I ran to her and tried to make her breath, but it was too late.

label: guilt
text: It happens to me quite often. I can't describe a particular case.

label: guilt
text: After being told that an ex-boyfriend had been hurt by my wearing something he had given me when I was with another guy. I was unaware of my actions really, as I had not considered the fact that he had given it to me, and might see me. I still respected his opinions of me.

label: guilt
text: I felt guilty when I was robbed of a friend's radio at Lilongwe bus depot after promising that I would keep it safe.

label: guilt
text: In the past I used to think that my mother was a very nagging person.  When I started living at the hostel we had little time to meet each other.  Whenever I went home she would take care of me.  I gradually realized that what she had done was for my own good.  So very time I saw her I felt guilty.

label: guilt
text: When I accepted a lunch invitation from a past male friend.

label: guilt
text: When I didn't bring my girlfriend home one night. Later she told me that a cardriver solicited her.

label: guilt
text: I am not good enough to join any team to play sport for the class.

label: guilt
text: When a mistake occurred at work which I was not responsible for.  This was disclosed later.

label: guilt
text: One day I found an incontinent man in the ward. This patient had a guardian who couldn't give him a bath. So I just left him like that but felt guilty until I went back to give him a bath.

label: guilt
text: I was looking after a child and she fell down because I was not paying her much attention.  One side of her face got bruised.

label: guilt
text: I wrote a bad letter to someone concerning our relationship which we created ourselves.

label: guilt
text: When one of my lovers told me that I was a flirt.

label: guilt
text: I felt it when playing I pushed my brother and he fell down cutting himself in pieces of tile.

label: guilt
text: My son drank four pills of diazepam every two hours instead of amidophen.

label: guilt
text: Finding out that I have misunderstood other people.

label: guilt
text: Guilt conscious struck me when I failed my Standard Two Examinations in 1972. I knew that I would suffer the consequences of what I had been doing during class hours: thus playing with friends and sometimes not even going to school.

label: guilt
text: When I applied for a false travelling claim allowance and later I thought that I would be found out.

label: guilt
text: Many years ago a friend wanted me to with her to southern Europe and I preferred to travel alone.  I felt guilty because I wanted to go on my own.

label: guilt
text: When my behaviour was immoral - thinking about sex.

label: guilt
text: Borrowing a car, and then having a minor accident (breaking a headlight).

label: guilt
text: My mother accused me of not visiting her enough when she was in hospital for an eye operation.

label: guilt
text: Incomprehension and repression towards a child's behaviour, commonly not accepted, and making the child cry.

label: guilt
text: I was involved in a ... attempt on a man I had developed a close warming relationship with. Although I knew I had done everything I could and that his progress of a \normal\" life was poor I felt √°|guilty as if I could have done more."

label: guilt
text: When I moved away from home.

label: guilt
text: Yesterday I broke my sister's raio. She hears it always when she has school examinations and now she has examinations.

label: guilt
text: I slapped my sister's daughter and after several hours, she had a high temperature and she ended up being admitted in hospital.

label: guilt
text: When I forgot to take out money for my mother. She asked me what she would do, because I had messed up her program for the following day.

label: guilt
text: Carried out a vandalistic act on some windows at an old army location.

label: guilt
text: Not helping parents enough at home and at the farm - this has happened many times.

label: guilt
text: I reproached my mother's cooking and criticised her personality, and she felt hurt and depressed.

label: guilt
text: When my uncle and my neighbour came home under police escort.

label: guilt
text: Decided at the last minute not to do something that I said I would do with a person.

label: guilt
text: Not doing well in the examn.

label: guilt
text: About not helping my sister when she asked me to help her on her chemistry class. I pretended to be busy.

label: guilt
text: When once my mother asked me to do some work for her at home because she was busy and moreover this work was to be done by a man. But it remained undone.

label: guilt
text: Feeling guilt after greed, buying chocolate and pigging out to the point of feeling sick, especially as I am fat.

label: guilt
text: Not thanking relatives for a favor done.

label: guilt
text: Not being able to help my friend.

label: guilt
text: While playing a ball game, I made a mistake and we lost the game.

label: guilt
text: A very, very close friend of mine used to come to my room to      see me and I naver bothered to pay him a visit.  One day he asked me the reason behind this and I gave him a shirt.

label: guilt
text: I promised my friends that I would take care of something, but I kept forgetting about it.  When they asked me about it, I promised to do it immediately.  However, I got started only after a couple of months.  I felt that I had betrayed my friends.

label: guilt
text: When I was young, I stole some money from my mother's purse. It wasn't very much, but I can remember when she found it gone I felt very guilty.

label: guilt
text: When I was starting in romance with my husband, we went out to curt, and we stayed in the car \making love\". At the time I was √°|seventeen and I was very immature until a day I lost my √°|virginity."

label: guilt
text: When I got associated with a boy one year ago, I neglected my best friend. When the relation with this boy finished she behaved very easy-going towards me. I felt guilty then.

label: guilt
text: While trying to get my little brother over a ditch, he fell on his head and started crying.  I was scared of having caused him permanent injury.

label: guilt
text: When I promised to visit my boyfriend and I didn't fulfil the promise.

label: guilt
text: I send a word to my boss through my servant telling him that I would not report for work as I was not feeling well and that the   doctor had refused to give me sick leave.  My intention was actually to go out of Lusaka for a week-end.  I left the same day and the following morning my boss found me in Mongu.  I felt guilty when asked to explain things on my return.

label: guilt
text: I was working as a secretary.  My boss was to go to give a lecture, and wanted me to give him the exact address of the place.

label: guilt
text: Car accident, hurt three of my closest family.

label: guilt
text: When I was a little girl about eight years old I broke the bey from a closed. Mother asked who did it. I said that it wasn't me, as I almost never lied, and my brother did it more frequently in spite my brother denieing it my mother gave him a few slaps.

label: guilt
text: I felt guilty when I said bad things to my sister, I had not intended to do so.  She cried a lot and later she fell ill and I felt responsible for her illness.

label: guilt
text: When I caused needless anxiety to a person close to me because of my lack of self-insight.

label: guilt
text: When my uncle found me having sexual intercourse with a distant relative of mine in the sitting room, on the couch.  I failed to stop and get up, I carried on.

label: guilt
text: When I was 4, we spent our holidays at the seaside. My sister and her friend wanted to go to a bay on an undangerous way. I wanted to arrive before them and went on a shorter, but more dangerous way. When I arrived, I found nobody there. I waited for a long time, but nobody came. On my way back I met my mother who had been searching for me desperatly. She did not scold me, but I saw how much she had worried (herself).

label: guilt
text: Peeping.

label: guilt
text: When I don't justify the confidence of people that I respect.

label: guilt
text: I was spending a few days at my aunt's place.  One night I got home very late, I had told them I was going to a party but I went to another place.  They were very worried.

label: guilt
text: A neighbour complained about smoke from my backyard incinerator entering his house after a change of wind direction. I lit the fire after originally checking that the wind would not blow the smoke in that direction.

label: guilt
text: I encouraged my brother to play football and he was hurt while playing the game.

label: guilt
text: One day I shouted at my brother who didn't do any wrong to me only that I had a disappointment from a friend and projected it on to him. He cried and I felt guilty after sometime.

label: guilt
text: During a discussion I reacted very aggressively and so I made it impossible to continue discussing.

label: guilt
text: When I took the car of someone without saying it to him.

label: guilt
text: I've always defended my sister when needed, at the expense of my brother. This has led to feelings of guilt towards him.

label: guilt
text: When I shirked the gymnastic lesson I met the director of our school who asked me what I was doing.

label: guilt
text: When I have sometimes been unfair to my parents, when I have happened to deceive them over some trifling things.

label: guilt
text: I was out with a friend in a place where it was very, very busy. When we wanted to go I bumped a person, who dropped his glass beer I offered a new one but he didn't accept it.

label: guilt
text: I forgot my mother's and sister's birthdays (they fall on the same day).

label: guilt
text: During a ski tour with a friend, we two had drunk too much. When we went down the slope on ski, I lost my friend who had lost his way. I thought that something must have happened to him (he finally arrived but after a very long time).

label: guilt
text: I do not study enough as I do not understand it properly.

label: guilt
text: Guilt at often being unable to visit a close relative in hospital after her death I felt very guilty and wished I had done more.

label: guilt
text: When I did not defend my close friend when my father degraded him. I felt guilty for allowing my father to get away with his actions and for the hurt my friend felt. I cleared the matter up with my father a few weeks later.

label: guilt
text: I felt guilty at being part of the successful people. Felt guilty at being a student when other people were not. Guilt about being a potential success in various areas of society. (So stupid this emotion)

label: guilt
text: One night, I went out with some friends for dinner and I did not tell my parents that I would come back late.  I thought of phoning but in the end I did not.  When I arrived home, my parents were very worried.

label: guilt
text: I've had three midterms in the past two weeks and I hardly studied for any of them (like 1 or 2 days) I feel guilty that I hadn't studied and I got C's on all of them.

label: guilt
text: While travelling in a bus with an invalid ticket, I got caught.

label: guilt
text: I wanted to get rid of a bad habit and it seemed that I had succeeded.  However a year later I got the bad habit again.  I felt  useless as I always found excuses to explain my behaviour.  As a result I felt guilty.

label: guilt
text: My schoolmates were teasing a pupil who was not able to defend himself very well; I should have taken his part.

label: guilt
text: I felt guilty one day when I stole a slice of bread in a cafeteria.

label: guilt
text: I felt guilty at not having practised the piano.  I waste my teacher's time and guidance.

label: guilt
text: I had a small argument with a relative and some other people got implicated.  It resulted in a proper row.

label: guilt
text: When I copy someone else's problem set.

label: guilt
text: Telling friends about your nickname.

label: guilt
text: When my husband talked about the restrictions he will have to accept in his life to make our marriage work.  I felt that it was directed at me as it was me who had demanded the changes.  We were with a marriage counsellor then.

label: guilt
text: When I flew out to my mother and made rude remarks because I felt so tense (studied too hard for an examination).

label: guilt
text: I chatted up with a girl who I didn't love. She however was fallen in love with me. I felt responsible for her sorrow.

label: guilt
text: I was entrusted with an object and while using it I handled it carelessly and it broke.

label: guilt
